dc:date  a      owl:AnnotationProperty .

gomodel:SYNGO_1311  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: The work shows CDH-9 immunofluorescence in the proximity of synaptic processes. Transfected expression of a tagged version of the CDH-9 indicates a discrete localization of the recombinantly expressed product outside but close to synaptic cluster. Overall evidence suggest targeted expression. Figure 8 highlights shRNA knock down of the CDH-9 proteins exerts a disruption of synaptic structure supporting synaptic function of the protein as assessed by quantitative morphometric EM.\n\n3/7/2017 Pim\n- Fig.5C shows the homophilic adhesive property of Cadh9\n- Fig.6/7/8 shows that pre-synaptic Cadh9 regulates postsynaptic development and vice versa. In SynGO we have a term synapse adhesion between pre- and post-synapse (GO:0099560) and I think this is very appropriate.. Experimental description: Mouse in utero poratin are explicitly mentioned in the methods but the culture method cited in the supplementary indicates rats and methods and figures do not clarify this.\n\n3/2/2017 Pim\n- Overexpressed protein is of mouse species. Literal \"cDNA encoding the predicted full-length cadherin-9 gene described in GenBank NM_009869.1 was amplified from a P7 mouse hippocampal cDNA library.\"\n- The species selection here can be either rat (species of neurons and KD protein) or mouse (species of over-expressed protein). I chose the mouse species since this has a reviewed Uniprot (SwissProt) record whereas rat does not." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-3185-5709" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-7351-8706" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0755-5899" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0938-8534" ;
        dc:date           "2018-06-06" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_1311" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

